-- Erste Leads Czech Shares Higher After Buy Recommendation at VTB
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-17T07:54:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/erste-leads-czech-shares-higher-after-buy-recommendation-at-vtb.html
Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  rose for a third
day, leading Czech shares higher after the Austrian lender was
rated buy in new coverage at VTB Capital.  The stock climbed 0.9 percent to 381.90 koruna by 9:44 a.m.
in  Prague , adding to a 1.3 percent advance in the previous two
days. The 14-member  PX (PX)  equity index, in which Erste has a 20
percent weighting, increased 0.4 percent to 905.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  